<p>Why try to beat them</p>

<p>When a million tried?</p>

<p>I remember reading this somewhere on George Hotz blog. Since then it has become one of my favorite quotes (I think it‚Äôs from a song or something) whenever I‚Äôm thinking of doing something that‚Äôs basically too much or sounds nuts like ‚Äúabolishing the education system‚Äù. I know I‚Äôm not the first to think of this or try to do it but someone has to beat it even if a million tried (and failed).</p>

<p>I‚Äôm not an anarchist. I‚Äôm not talking about the whole education system at once or preventing people from going to schools, but also I don‚Äôt like the fact that this is the de facto of education and people sort of just agreed upon it. It is worthwhile to think about what people consider the normal or the standard way of doing things. Most of the great inventions were just a product of that.</p>

<p>To help you trace back the things that led me to think of this is that at the end of college I just realized how much time and effort can be saved both in the long and the short run simply by adopting smarter methods for education. I‚Äôm not exaggerating if I said I‚Äôve learned more than 90% of my courses from YouTube and other websites  and honestly I can see why it‚Äôs not possible for someone to get to 100% if given the right guidance which is basically the job of your professors and teachers but that is not happening. Besides, I really hated my college and this is my way of directing these negative feelings towards a good cause.
As a start I genuinely want to fully replace my faculty (fmsi) with an online platform that contains the information, knowledge, resources and method of evaluation for an equivalent of a bachelor degree in math computer science and statistics 
I think these fields are the best start to a much larger change that will make education more efficient, flexible and accessible for all.Computer science courses by nature are the easiest to be completely made online. There‚Äôs a plethora of resources already available however for math and statistics that might be harder.
This doesn‚Äôt have to be super complex or even useful from the start I won‚Äôt let my desire for perfection to hold me from getting started this time similar to this blog it will grow and I‚Äôll try to create the right environment for it to grow</p>

